or Economist Podcasts+ now and get 50% off your subscription with &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.economist.comhttps://subscribenow.economist.com/podcasts-plus?purchaseRedirect=economist.com%2Faudio%2Fpodcasts%2Fonboarding%3Fpodcast%3Dchecks-and-balance&quot;>;our limited time offer&lt;/a>;.&lt;/p>;&lt;p>;You will not be charged until Economist Podcasts+ launches. If you&#39;re already a subscriber to &lt;i>;The Economist&lt;/i>;, you&#39;ll have full access to all our shows as part of your subscription. For more information about Economist Podcasts+, including how to get access, please visit our &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.economist.comhttps://myaccount.economist.com/s/article/What-is-Economist-Podcasts&quot;>;FAQs page&lt;/a>;.&lt;/p>;&lt;p>;The Economist Live is coming to New York and Washington, DC this October. &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.economist.com/americanevents&quot;>;Learn more&lt;/a>; about our live events. &lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 23 Sep 2023 17:27:03 +0800</pubDate></item><item><title><![CDATA[Why shoplifting is on the rise in Britain | Britain]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.economist.com/britain/2023/09/22/why-shoplifting-is-on-the-rise-in-britain]]><description> &lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl/?url=www.economist.com/img/b/1280/720/90/media-assets/image/20230923_BRP507.jpg&quot;/>;&lt;div>;&lt;/div>;&lt;p data-caps=&quot;initial&quot;>;&lt;span data-caps=&quot;initial&quot;>;T&lt;/span>;&lt;small>;he thief&lt;/small>; was in no hurry.在伦敦南部布里克斯顿一条繁忙的街道上，他看到商店前面摆着一堆电风扇，他慢悠悠地走进去，把一个夹在腋下，然后慢悠悠地走了出去。收银员摆弄着一台坏掉的自助收银台，没有注意到。 If she had, it is unlikely she would have tried to stop him.&lt;/p>;&lt;p>;In an era of generally falling crime, shoplifting is rising.截至 2023 年 3 月的一年里，警方报告了 342,343 起此类案件，比上一年增加了 24%。毫无疑问，这个数字只占商店盗窃总数的一小部分。 The British Retail Consortium (&lt;small>;brc&lt;/small>;) has warned retail crime is “soaring across the country.”廉价时尚连锁店 Primark 本月表示，入店行窃已经削弱了其利润。约翰·刘易斯合伙企业（John Lewis Partnership，拥有商店和维特罗斯超市）主席莎伦·怀特夫人 (Dame Sharon White) 将其描述为一种“流行病”。 &lt;/p>;&lt;div>;&lt;div>;&lt;div id=&quot;econ-1&quot;>;&lt;/div>;&lt;/div>;&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;The reported statistics are less dramatic than they might at first appear: they are, more or less, back to pre-pandemic levels.当英国人被封锁时，入店行窃急剧下降。然而，过去十年此类犯罪逐渐增多。 And the &lt;small>;brc&lt;/small>; says in some cities retail crime is rising particularly sharply.&lt;/p>;&lt;p>;Patchy data don&#39;t reveal exactly who is swiping from shops, nor why.生活成本危机常常被归咎于这一问题。但包括学术界在内的轶事证据表明，这仅占一小部分。 The Association of Convenience Stores (&lt;small>;acs&lt;/small>;) which represents 33,500 small, local shops, says most shoplifters are repeat offenders, often with drug or alcohol problems. &lt;/p>;&lt;p>;Emmeline Taylor, a professor of criminology at City University, says such thieves may steal to order, after first getting “a shopping list” from a criminal gang.受欢迎的商品包括酒类、婴儿配方奶粉、糖果和肉类，一些商店称这些商品被大量盗走，销往其他地方。团伙参与其他一些类型的盗窃的可能性要小得多，尤其是入室盗窃，这种盗窃行为在过去 20 年来一直在下降。 &lt;/p>;&lt;p>;A change to the law in 2014 may, unwittingly, have encouraged gangs to recruit shoplifters, while also spurring individuals to steal for themselves.它将价值 200 英镑（245 美元）或以下的商店行窃定为简易犯罪，并在地方法院（而不是皇家法院）进行审判。这可能阻碍了警方调查此类犯罪。 &lt;/p>;&lt;p>;The police are more likely to pursue repeat offenders, who are often given brief, successive prison sentences.这收效甚微。相反，政府应该对那些为了资助毒瘾而偷窃的人实施戒毒令。这些努力还有助于解决零售商报告的另一个趋势：商店扒手似乎变得更加咄咄逼人，甚至准备威胁使用暴力，这使得员工不愿与他们对抗。 &lt;/p>;&lt;div>;&lt;div>;&lt;div id=&quot;econ-2&quot;>;&lt;/div>;&lt;/div>;&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;Retailers are working more with police. John Lewis and other shops are funding a project, dubbed “Pegasus”, that will see more &lt;small>;cctv&lt;/small>; footage and other intelligence passed on to officers. Graham Wynn, assistant director of business and regulation for the &lt;small>;brc,&lt;/small>; calls that “worthy” but says he wants the police to “give greater priority to retail crime.”&lt;/p>;&lt;p>;Is that realistic?利兹大学犯罪学教授格雷厄姆·法雷尔 (Graham Farrell) 指出，只有大约 2% 的犯罪（各种类型）会被定罪。因此，对于商店来说，更有意义的做法是从一开始就专注于让他们更难做出承诺。他说，大商店里摆满诱人的商品“创造了巨大的犯罪机会”。自助结账不会有帮助。 &lt;/p>;&lt;p>;The most effective measures include fitting more “hot products” with security tags, moving high-value items away from entrances and arranging aisles so staff can see down them more easily.研究人员指出，派人在门口迎接购物者可以减少盗窃，尽管只有高端商店才会这样做。并非所有的小罪犯都像布里克斯顿的扇子小偷一样无耻。 &lt;span data-ornament=&quot;ufinish&quot;>;■&lt;/span>;&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 23 Sep 2023 17:27:03 +0800</pubDate> </item><item><title><![CDATA[America’s missing doctors | Graphic detail]]></title><link/><![CDATA[https://www.economist.com/graphic-detail/2023/09/22/americas-missing-doctors]]><description> &lt;img src=&quot;https://images.weserv.nl/?url=www.economist.com/img/b/1280/720/90/media-assets/image/20230923_WOT683.png&quot;/>;&lt;div>;&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;&lt;i>;To read more of The Economist&#39;s data journalism visit our &lt;a href=&quot;https://www.economist.com/graphic-detail/&quot;>;Graphic detail&lt;/a>; page.&lt;/i>;&lt;/p>;&lt;p data-caps=&quot;initial&quot;>;&lt;span data-caps=&quot;initial&quot;>;I&lt;/span>;&lt;small>;N 1920 THERE&lt;/small>; were 5m people in America over the age of 65, around 5% of the total.如今有5600万，比例已上升至17%。世界范围内的人口结构也正在发生类似的巨大变化：联合国预测，到 2050 年，北美和欧洲 25% 的人口可能超过 65 岁。因此，对老年医学专业医生的需求正在上升，而在许多地方，供应量也不断增加。正在上升以匹配。但在美国则不然。老年病学是内科中最不受欢迎的专业（见图表），该国正面临着短缺。为什么？ &lt;/p>;&lt;figure data-infographic->;&lt;/figure>;&lt;figure>;&lt;iframe height=&quot;NaN&quot; src=&quot;https://infographics.economist.com/2023/20230923_WOC683/&quot;>;&lt;/iframe>;&lt;/figure>;&lt;p>;Shortages are looming in a range of fields.预计大约五分之二的美国医生将在未来十年内达到退休年龄，这可能会加剧这一问题。但老年医学的前景尤其令人担忧。根据将学生医生与医院进行匹配的国家住院医师匹配计划，今年美国老年医学奖学金计划的 411 个名额中只有 177 个名额被填补。相比之下，一些奖学金，例如肿瘤学和心血管疾病奖学金，已经全部满员。 &lt;/p>;&lt;p>;The American Geriatrics Society expects that 12,320 geriatricians will be needed to care for elderly Americans by 2030, but that only 7,580 will be practising.部分问题在于，实习医生发现治疗老年患者的回报低于治疗年轻患者的回报：老年人往往患有复杂的长期病症，无法完全恢复健康。不过，在其他国家，尤其是欧洲，招聘问题要简单得多。 In Finland, for example, the number of geriatricians rose by 70% between 2010 and 2020.&lt;/p>;&lt;div>;&lt;div>;&lt;div id=&quot;econ-1&quot;>;&lt;/div>;&lt;/div>;&lt;/div>;&lt;p>;America&#39;s shortfall probably comes down to money.老年科医生的平均工资低于不需要完成额外进修培训的医生：他们的工资比普通内科医生低 9%，比住院医生（治疗住院病人）低 14%。老年病学家还表示，他们在美国老年人公共健康保险公司医疗保险（Medicare）方面处于不利地位。协调不同专家之间的复杂护理的医生无法获得与其他专家相同程度的医疗保险补偿。 &lt;/p>;&lt;p>;Proposed changes to Medicare could lead to more generous reimbursement of doctors, like geriatricians, who help manage these chronic health issues (though it would also reduce funding for other specialists).六年之内，美国大多数婴儿潮一代将有资格享受医疗保险，这给这项服务带来了更大的负担。但是否有足够的医生来照顾他们似乎存在严重疑问。 &lt;span data-ornament=&quot;ufinish&quot;>;■&lt;/span>;&lt;/p>;</description><pubDate> Sat, 23 Sep 2023 17:27:03 +0800</pubDate></item></channel></rss>